simpledb

Class HeapPage

  • java.lang.Object
    • simpledb.HeapPage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Page

    public class HeapPage
extends java.lang.Object
implements Page
    A HeapPage is a collection of Tuples. A fixed-size memory space is used for each HeapPage. A HeapFile consists of HeaPages. The HeapPage class implements the Page interface that is used by BufferPool.
    See Also:
    HeapFile, BufferPool

    • Constructor Detail

      • HeapPage

        public HeapPage(HeapPageId id,
                byte[] data)
         throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a HeapPage from a byte array storing data read from disk. This byte array contains (1) a 4-byte integer representing the number of Tuples assigned to the HeapPage, (2) a sequence of integer values each of which indicates where the corresponding Tuple is stored in the byte array, (3) a free space reserved for storing additional Tuples, and (4) a sequence of Tuples.
        Parameters:
        id - the ID of the HeapPage.
        data - a byte array storing the data to read.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        See Also:
        Database.getCatalog(), Catalog.getTupleDesc(int), BufferPool.PAGE_SIZE

    • Method Detail

      • getPageData

        public byte[] getPageData()
        Generates a byte array representing the contents of this HeapPage. This method is used to serialize this HeapPage to disk.

        The invariant here is that it should be possible to pass the byte array generated by this method to the HeapPage constructor and have it produce an identical HeapPage.

        Specified by:

        Returns:
        a byte array correspond to the content of this HeapPage.

        public static byte[] createEmptyPageData()
